<h1>Sonia Kovalevsky Day</h1>

<p>
Dear Parents and Teachers,
</p>

<p>
You're invited to bring your female students to the Sonia Kovalevsky
Math Day at Worcester Polytechnic Institute on Saturday, May 7,
2011.  This event for female students in grades 6-10 willl include
workshops on several different interesting topics and an individual
competition.  The Sonia Kovalevsky Math Day is meant to encourage
girls to continue their study in mathematics and to expose them to new
and interesting topics in math.  All participants in this year's event
will receive a free t-shirt.  Lunch will also be provided.
</p>

<p>
Regeistration will take place from 9:45-10:00am at Stratton hall.  The
day will conclude with an awards ceremony which will take place from
4:00-5:00 pm.  Parents are encouraged to attend the awards ceremony.
</p>

<table>
  <tr>
    <td> Tentative Schedule of Events </td>
  </tr>
