    <td> Awards Ceremony </td>
</table>
	
<br />
<p>
The workshops offered include Codes and Ciphers, How to cut a birthday
cake, Cool jobs in math, Math Puzzles, Modeling Networks with Math,
What is a knot, and Hands on Geometry.  The workshops will be tailored
to each grade level.  The individual competition will feature problems
meant to stimulate the girls and get them thinking about new and exciting mathematical ideas.
</p>

<p>
The event is being run by female students and professors wfrom
Worcester Polytechnic Institute and is genorously sponsored by the
Association of Women in Mathematics, the WPI Mathematical Sciences
Department, and the Center for Industrial Mathematics and Statistics.
</p>


<p>
If interested, please register your children or students on the online
application.
</p>

